reviews.text:
Family Run Noodle Shop.
A small noodle shop operates by a couple. Their specialty is fried chicken ball and braised pig nickle. Can serves with noodle or rice. Noodle available in soup or dry with soya sauce. The chicken ball use thigh meat to wrap ginger paste to form a ball shape and deep fried. The skin is crispy and meat still soft, kids and those who like fried food will love it. The soup is chicken broth which tastes rather light, so those who like richer taste may consider the dry version with special soya sauce.
The pig nickle is cook until it is very soft. So soft that it almost fall apart when it was pick up with chopsticks. As it is braised, all the flavors penetrate deep into the meat, tasty!
Worth to try!

這檔酥炸雞球撈麵非常好食正呀👍👍
